[normal]The beauty of this approach is the ability to c
[normal]reate time and location restrictions for cycle safety.  
[normal]The key for a viable city and road share model is good data to determine what times and locations we can de-conflict. 
[normal]The locations will need to be dynamic as TfL &amp; other
[normal]s will need to 
[normal]get a handle on
[normal] cycle 
[normal]behaviour 
[normal]data and which locations and times we need to protect from HGV’s .  This approach can provide a safer freight routing requirement.  i.e. hauliers have to sign up for the safer freight scheme which could be 
[normal]a 
[normal]volunteer 
[normal]service 
[normal]initially bas
[normal]ed on their TFL FORS membership (Fleet Operators Recognition Scheme).
[normal]  Alternatively this could be a compulsory requirement for construction project sites.
[normal]PIE with City University have been researching (own time) the data that is readily available that wi
[normal]ll enable us to create a good understand of the cycle behaviour model.  This
[normal] would include 
[normal]which roads/routes/areas by time of day and day of the week do we ne
