[normal]Any recommendations for action by the Government or others which you would like the committee to consider.[bold]My 
[normal]recommendations would be to change the current LLCS
[normal] (London Lorry Control Scheme)
[normal] to be day time routing also instead of just night-t
[normal]ime or change the network restrictions for day time.  (technically we can handle the restrictions data and provide the comp
[normal]liant routes by time and day).
[normal]Other recommendations that will be easier and quick to implement that can work would be to enforce all construction sites/projects to have a complaint routing service for HGV contractors vehicles that includes time and 
[normal]location restrictions on the cycle network.  Therefore ensuring construction vehicles are not on these roads at the key times and locations as cyclist
[normal] based on a good cyclist data model
[normal].  
[normal]I recommend that the restriction areas are set up so they can be ch
[normal]anged as we will need flexibility to 
[normal]assign key locations as we better understand the vulnerable areas and behaviours.   
[normal]We need more data on which locations that is best for HGVs to avoid and at what times and days of the week so the system really works. 
